                          <KeepTogether>true</KeepTogether>
                          <Paragraphs>
                            <Paragraph>
                              <TextRuns>
                                <TextRun>
                                  <Value>The undertakings herein shall be honored and binding on the Buyer or any of the Buyer’s successor or assignee of a part or all of the Buyer’s rights and obligations under the Sale and Purchase Agreement or receives the transfer of the corresponding House/land use right from the Buyer, to sustain the Common Area of the Project. The Buyer is obliged to (i) provide all the complete contents of this Letter to the successor/assignee and procure that the successor/assignee will assume all of the Buyer’s rights and obligations under this Letter; and (ii) hold harmless the Developer and the Sub-developer from any disputes, complaints or damages caused by the Buyer's successor/assignee regarding the implementation of the contents stated in this Letter. Unless otherwise approved by the Developer, the Buyer shall procure that the successor/transferee mentioned above will sign and submit a written letter of confirmation and undertaking in the form of this Letter before receiving the transfer of rights or at the request of the Developer.</Value>
                                  <Style>
                                    <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                                    <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                                    <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                                    <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                                    <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                                  </Style>
                                </TextRun>
                              </TextRuns>
                              <Style />
                            </Paragraph>
                          </Paragraphs>
                          <rd:DefaultName>Textbox304</rd:DefaultName>
                          <Style>
